# Result Analysis 2.4: Current Full Generation Quality

## 0. Scope

This analysis covers the documents that had been generated under `cache/generation/final_candidates/` after the current full-generation run.

At the time of review, 13 guide candidates existed:

- `accessibility-highlight-overlay`
- `adaptor-framework`
- `addon-manager`
- `animated-image-view`
- `animation`
- `focus-manager`
- `i-scroll-bar`
- `image`
- `image-loader`
- `image-view`
- `input-event`
- `input-field`
- `interactive-view`

This is not yet the complete set of all planned document features. The conclusion below is therefore about the current generated subset only.

## 1. Executive Summary

Overall quality is meaningfully better than the early Phase 2.3 outputs. Most generated guides are useful, structurally complete, and aligned with the dali-ui app-guide premise.

However, the current quality gate is not reliable enough yet because it has two opposite problems:

- It blocks several good documents due to validator false positives.
- It allows a few documents that are syntactically plausible but not ideal as public app-facing guides.

The most important remaining work is not more generation prompt tuning. The next high-leverage improvement is validator precision:

- distinguish real prompt leakage from valid public API/domain terms such as `PLACEHOLDER`;
- resolve C++ backticked type/signature tokens correctly;
- validate enum/property owners exactly without dropping scope;
- detect guide-surface mismatch for integration/platform APIs;
- add lightweight code-block completeness checks.

## 2. Current Final Report Interpretation

`cache/generation/final_report.md` reports:

| Metric | Count |
|---|---:|
| Generated candidates | 13 |
| Publish-ready | 10 |
| Generated but not publish-ready | 3 |

The 3 blocked documents are:

- `animated-image-view`
- `image-view`
- `input-field`

Important: all three are blocked mainly because the validator treats `placeholder` as prompt leakage. In these documents, `placeholder` is a legitimate DALi UI image/text API concept, not internal prompt leakage.

## 3. Per-Document Quality Assessment

### accessibility-highlight-overlay

Verdict: usable but surface-sensitive.

API correctness:

- The methods used in the guide match `repos/dali-ui/dali-ui-foundation/integration-api/accessibility-highlight-overlay.h`.
- `OverlayHighlightMode`, `AccessibilityHighlightOverlay`, `SetCustomHighlight`, `ResetCustomHighlight`, `UpdateOverlay`, `HideOverlay`, `SetOverlayMode`, and `GetOverlayMode` are real public integration API entries.

Issues:

- The validator warning for `Dali::Actor&` is a false positive. It is a C++ type spelling, not an unknown API token.
- This is an integration-facing API. The guide is careful to say that app-facing UI should remain `Dali::Ui::View` based, but its presence as a normal app guide should be reviewed by tier/surface policy.

Recommended action:

- Keep the document if integration APIs are intended to appear in the generated app-guide set.
- Otherwise mark it as an advanced/integration surface in document planning rather than treating it as a normal component guide.

### adaptor-framework

Verdict: good app-entry guide with validator false positives.

API correctness:

- `Dali::Application::New`, `InitSignal`, `MainLoop`, `Quit`, `GetResourcePath`, `GetLanguage`, and `GetRegion` match the adaptor public API.
- The guide correctly uses `Dali::Ui::View` as the root UI object.

Issues:

- Validator warnings for `void(Dali::Application` are false positives caused by callback-signature text inside backticks.
- The examples use `DALI_EXPORT_API`. That is common in DALi examples, but compile validation should eventually confirm that the include set exposes it in each snippet context.

Recommended action:

- Keep.
- Add signature-token normalization to Phase 2.4.

### addon-manager

Verdict: technically rich, but questionable as an app-facing guide.

API correctness:

- The guide uses `Dali::Integration::AddOnManager`, `Dali::AddOnInfo`, `EnumerateAddOns`, `GetAddOnInfo`, `LoadAddOns`, `GetAddOn`, and `GetGlobalProc` in ways that match `repos/dali-core/dali/integration-api/addon-manager.h`.

Issues:

- This is integration/platform-level API, not a typical dali-ui application feature.
- Some procedures such as typed procedure invocation are advanced and should not look like ordinary app-development guidance unless platform integration is part of the target audience.

Recommended action:

- Keep only if `platform-integration` guides are intentionally generated in the selected tier/profile.
- Otherwise suppress or mark as advanced through document planning.

### animated-image-view

Verdict: useful but not fully publish-ready.

API correctness:

- Most API usage is correct: `AnimatedImageView::New`, `SetResourceUrl`, `SetResourceUrls`, playback methods, loop/speed/stop behavior, fitting/sampling/masking/loading methods, and property constants map to the public headers.
- The validator's `placeholder` bug is a false positive. `SetPlaceholderUrl()` and `PLACEHOLDER_IMAGE` are real feature concepts.
- Warnings for `Dali::Ui::AnimatedImageView&` and `Dali::Vector<Dali::String>` are false positives caused by C++ type-token parsing.

Real issue:

- The example uses `Dali::Ui::UiColor(0xFFFFFFFF)`. `UiColor(uint32_t rgb, float a = 1.0f)` is documented as a hex RGB constructor, so an 8-hex ARGB/RGBA-looking literal is at best ambiguous and likely misleading. Prefer `UiColor(0xFFFFFF, 1.0f)` or the float constructor.

Recommended action:

- Fix validator false positives.
- Add a semantic color-literal validation rule for `UiColor(uint32_t rgb, ...)` examples.

### animation

Verdict: strong guide.

API correctness:

- The document uses the dali-ui animation convenience layer and keeps the app model `View` based.
- `AlphaFunction::EASE_IN`, `EASE_OUT`, `EASE_IN_OUT`, and `Animation::BAKE`, `DISCARD`, `BAKE_FINAL` are real DALi public API enum values.

Issues:

- All current validator warnings for this document are false positives caused by enum-owner resolution gaps.

Recommended action:

- Keep.
- Improve nested enum/static value resolution.

### focus-manager

Verdict: good guide with minor validator false positive.

API correctness:

- `FocusManager::Get`, `RequestFocus`, `SetCurrentFocusView`, `GetCurrentFocusView`, `MoveFocus`, `MoveFocusBackward`, `SetAsFocusGroup`, `IsFocusGroup`, `GetFocusGroup`, `SetFocusIndicatorActor`, `GetFocusIndicatorView`, `FocusChangedSignal`, `ClearFocus`, `SetClearFocusOnWindowFocusLost`, `GetClearFocusOnWindowFocusLost`, `GetLastFocusChangeDevice`, and `GetLastFocusChangeDeviceName` are consistent with `focus-manager.h`.

Issues:

- The validator warning for `Dali::Ui::FocusManager::MoveFocus(Dali::Ui::FocusDirection::FORWARD` is a false positive caused by a backticked function-call/signature fragment.

Recommended action:

- Keep.
- Improve function-call/signature parsing in backtick validation.

### i-scroll-bar

Verdict: good interface guide, assuming interface-level docs are wanted.

API correctness:

- `IScrollBar` methods used in the guide match the public interface.
- `ScrollBarVisibility` values are plausible and aligned with scrollable enum usage.


